MATCH_TOOL: Edit|Write
MATCH_PATTERN: apps/game-server/src/machines/(actions|cartridges)/.+\.ts$
MATCH_CONTENT: enqueue\.(raise|sendTo|assign|stopChild)
ADVISORY: |
  `enqueue` is only available inside `enqueueActions(fn)` — it is NOT passed
  to a plain `assign(fn)` wrapper or a bare action function. Calling
  `enqueue.raise(...)` / `enqueue.sendTo(...)` / `enqueue.assign(...)` /
  `enqueue.stopChild(...)` from inside `assign(({ context, event, enqueue }) => …)`
  fails silently: the raise never fires, the assign may still apply, and no
  XState error is surfaced.

  If the action needs BOTH a context patch AND a raise/sendTo, use
  `enqueueActions` and call `enqueue.assign({...})` instead of returning a
  patch:

    WRONG
      recordConfession: assign(({ context, event, enqueue }) => {
        enqueue.raise({ type: 'FACT.RECORD', fact });       // undefined
        return { posts: [...context.posts, post] };
      })

    RIGHT
      recordConfession: enqueueActions(({ context, event, enqueue }) => {
        enqueue.raise({ type: 'FACT.RECORD', fact });
        enqueue.assign({ posts: [...context.posts, post] });
      })

  Similarly, a plain `({ context, enqueue }) => { enqueue.raise(...) }`
  wrapper is not an action — xstate calls it with only `{ context, event }`.
  Always wrap with `enqueueActions()` when you need `enqueue`.

  Real cost: 2026-04-18 confessions T9. Three actions (recordConfession,
  emitConfessionPhaseStartedFact, emitConfessionPhaseEndedFact) were the
  wrong flavor. Symptom: "CONFESSION.POST appends a post" test failed with
  posts length 0; "groupChatOpen toggles" failed because assign() never
  reached its patch. All three fixed by switching `assign` / bare fn to
  `enqueueActions`.
